    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> cornflour </strong>and<strong> </strong>2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[4 tbsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>to a plate, season with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and a generous grind of<strong> pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>flour mix</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>marinated free range chicken thighs</strong> to the <strong>flour mix</strong>, then press firmly into the mixture,<strong> </strong>making sure to evenly coat them on both sides – this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p><p>Discard any remaining marinade</p>",
