    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>sriracha</strong> and <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a small heatproof bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Carefully pour the <strong>remaining cooking oil</strong> into the bowl, give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>chilli oil</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>brioche halves</strong> to a baking tray, cut side up, and put the tray in the oven for 4-5 min or until warmed through</p>",
